Siphamandla Goge is monitoring developments outside the former president's Nkandla home. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - With only three days to go before he has to hand himself over to authorities, former President Jacob Zuma is reportedly using this time to consult with his legal team in Durban. Zuma was found to be in contempt of court for his consistent refusal to appear before the State Capture Inquiry. READ: Religious leaders arrive in Nkandla to pray for Zuma Religious leaders and Zuma's supporters have gathered outside his Nkandla home to show their devotion and provide spiritual guidance. eNCA Senior Reporter, Siphamandla Goge shares more details in the video above.